The paper proposes a novel memory architecture for analyzing patient electronic health records using deep learning techniques. The paper focuses on the interpretability of the model and proposes a partitioning of the external memory space into a primary explicit memory block and a secondary blurred memory block. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), cybernetics (cs.CY), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
